While Walt Disney Productions continued releasing family-friendly films throughout the 1970s, such as ''[[Escape to Witch Mountain]]'' (1975) and ''[[Freaky Friday (1976 film)|Freaky Friday]]'' (1976), the films did not fare as well at the box office as earlier material. The animation studio, however, saw success with ''[[Robin Hood (1973 film)|Robin Hood]]'' (1973), ''[[The Rescuers]]'' (1977), and ''[[The Fox and the Hound]]'' (1981).
